
<p>Via a DF reader, here’s a 20-second clip from the 1993 classic<sup>*</sup> <em>Demolition Man</em> that exemplifies how today’s overly effusive, ever-affirming AI chatbots were presented as elements of a profoundly dystopic future by sci-fi writers just a few decades ago.</p>

<p><small><sup>*</sup>OK, OK — <em>cult</em> classic.</small></p>

